parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Continuously Variable Transmission (CVT) can cause the vehicle to lose acceleration, go into limp mode, and stall, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle goes into limp mode while accelerating uphill
the vehicle stalls
the transmission has issues with acceleration
the RPM gauge fluctuates
the transmission fluid needs to be replaced frequently
the vehicle loses the ability to downshift
and the vehicle loses acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TCM can cause the CVT to go into fail-safe mode, resulting in the vehicle losing acceleration, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The Malfunction Indicator Light (MIL) illuminates
the CVT goes into fail-safe mode
the vehicle loses acceleration
and the vehicle will not exit the fail-safe mode without dealership attention.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine and transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, lose acceleration, and pour carbon monoxide into the car, which can lead to accidents or endanger the lives of the occupants.
symptoms: The vehicle cuts off while driving
the vehicle pours carbon monoxide into the car
the transmission breaks down frequently
and the vehicle requires frequent repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power steering can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-miss situations.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes hard to turn
the power steering warning light illuminates
the vehicle loses power steering while driving
the power steering is restored after turning the engine off and back on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of an accident, potentially causing serious injury or death.
symptoms: The passenger airbag light is illuminated
the airbag system cannot be cleared
multiple codes are displayed on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause multiple systems to malfunction, leading to a loss of control or safety features.
symptoms: Multiple dash lights come on
the vehicle loses power
the engine cannot be shut off
the vehicle stops in the middle of testing and cannot be restarted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The frequent burning out of headlight bulbs can lead to reduced visibility, increased risk of accidents, and safety hazards, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Headlight bulbs burn out consistently within 6 months
requiring frequent repairs
multiple bulb failures at once
and difficulty seeing while driving at night.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can lead to a loss of critical information, such as speed, engine performance, and warning indicators, which can compromise vehicle safety and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The display including speedometer
tachometer
blinker
and multifunction display shuts down
resulting in a loss of critical information for the driver.
